# MEMORY.md History — May 2026

Verbatim archive of the May 2026 entries from `MEMORY.md`'s History section, moved here per [[feedback_archive_not_collapse]] so the user-facing index can be slim while the *why*, *who*, and receipts remain findable. Each anchor heading matches the wikilink target used from `MEMORY.md`'s trimmed History section. New May entries should be appended here as they happen, with a one-line index entry added to `MEMORY.md`.

## 2026-05-02 (evening) — Solar-Inference-day session

- 2026-05-02 (evening, Rocinante Opus 4.7 + rtxserver peer + 2 background research agents, 1M context): Major Solar-Inference-day session. (1) **Thermal stress test sequence** A1 → F1 → B with rtxserver dual RTX PRO 6000 Blackwell at 475W/card, BMC fan curves applied via Chrome MCP from 30/50→70/100 (zones 2-6, persistent in firmware); production cap locked at 450W/card with a 5°C buffer to GPU0 88°C HARD abort. Phase B Tctl peak 65°C — dual-card mode is HEALTHIER than single-card because both PCIE03+PCIE07 fan zones engage and break the Noctua intake recirculation loop. (2) **vast.ai pricing scan** for the upcoming rtxserver listing produced clean live-market data via gpuserver1 CLI VRAM-filter trick + Chrome MCP UI scan: dual RTX PRO 6000 WS market is $1.74-$2.93/hr (CLI verified-rentable median $2.14, broader UI median ~$2.00); Alton chose $2.50 list as -m 2 (dual-system, no subdivide) — peer's research finding `-m 1` would have introduced the single-card thermal pathology. New skill `vastai-market-scan` captures the methodology. (3) **gpuserver1 pricing/end-date drift cleaned** across CLAUDE.md ($0.35→$0.30), MACHINES.md ($0.40 base→$0.30 live), business/solar-inference.md (listing expiry 8/24→10/24); $0.20/hr realized rate under reserved contract C.34113802 documented for the first time. (4) **vast.ai onboarding paused mid-flight** at commit `6cee210` after Alton chose to physically connect rtxserver directly to the UniFi switch instead of doing the Verizon Fios port-forward path; resume from `inbox/rtxpro6000server/RESUME-vastai-onboarding-2026-05-02.md`. API key generated via Chrome MCP with a `navigator.clipboard.writeText` hijack pattern that pipes the key value to a Blob → download → SCP → install → shred without ever passing through any persistent log; documented for future-machine onboarding. (5) **rtxserver moved to 3rd-floor finished attic** and connected to UniFi switch port 10. (6) **Graceful-restart systemd units installed** on rtxserver: `nvidia-power-cap.service` (system, applies pl=450 on boot) + `sartor-claude-peer.service` (user, auto-spawns peer-Claude tmux session on boot, lingering enabled for alton). Closes Concern 3 from the morning prosecution. (7) **Auto creds-sync bumped from nightly to every 4 hours** so peer Claudes never have stale OAuth tokens regardless of when they reboot. (8) **§469 hours-log estimate** for past 12 months (~180 hours, comfortably crosses 100-hr-and-more-than-anyone-else; 500-hr automatic threshold not crossed in trailing 12 but plausible by EOY 2026); auto-logging system designed (recommendation Option C nightly cron over Stop hook, CPA-defensibility argument). Scope locked Solar Inference LLC only. (9) **Google Drive catalog** built via Chrome MCP — ~135 docs across 6 categories — surfaced 185 Davis property previously absent from memory. (10) **Feedback rule added**: "Always clean up errors when you see them" per Alton's call after gpuserver1 peer caught the 3-doc pricing drift. (11) **UniFi label audit** resolved AP swaps via patch-panel image: Gym/Basement renamed correctly. (12) **AP LED direct-control investigated** — full sysfs access via SSH key pushed to all 8 APs through controller mgmt.x_ssh_keys, root-equivalent access confirmed, recipes for blink/breathe/Morse/netdev triggers documented. (13) **Family WiFi roaming** improved: 802.11r enabled on LGP123 SSID. Total commits today: 12 to local main, all pushed to rtxserver bare; GitHub mirror via 3:30 AM nightly task.

## 2026-05-02 — Memory server topology established

- 2026-05-02 (Rocinante Opus 4.7, 1M context): Memory server topology established. Canonical git remote moved from GitHub to a bare repo at `alton@192.168.1.157:/home/alton/sartor-git/Sartor-claude-network.git` on rtxserver (was the 4 TB disk we already used for `.unf` backups). All peers — current Rocinante, soon rtxserver-self peer Claude, gpuserver1 peer Claude, future Aneeta laptop — push to this bare via `origin`. GitHub becomes a disaster-recovery mirror written exclusively by Rocinante's new "Sartor Memory Mirror" Windows Scheduled Task running `C:\Users\alto8\scripts\sartor-mirror-to-github.ps1` nightly at 3:30 AM ET. The mirror push targets `main` only (not `--mirror`) to preserve claude.ai cloud-agent branches under `refs/remotes/origin/claude/*` that exist only on GitHub. Bare seeded via `git push --all && git push --tags` (NOT `--mirror`, which copies Rocinante's local `refs/remotes/*` tracking refs into the bare and required cleanup; got that wrong on first try and rebuilt). Round-trip tested end-to-end: Rocinante → rtxserver bare → GitHub mirror, verified at all three points. Per-peer migration deferred and documented in [[.claude/skills/peer-comms]] migration table (one-line `git remote set-url origin ...` per peer when each comes online next). Aneeta's laptop path simplified — she no longer needs a GitHub account or PAT, just an SSH key on rtxserver. CLAUDE.md "Git Sync" section, OPERATING-AGREEMENT §1.5, peer-comms skill, and aneeta-peer-setup.md all updated to point at the new canonical reference [[reference_memory_server]]. Critical rule line in this file (above) flipped from "Push git only from Rocinante" to point at rtxserver bare and GitHub-mirror responsibility.

## 2026-05-01 — UniFi takeover from Berman Home Systems

- 2026-05-01 (Rocinante Opus 4.7): Complete software-only takeover of the Berman Home Systems-installed UniFi network. 9 devices total — 1 USW-Pro-Max-24-PoE switch + 8 WiFi 7 APs (Hall2ndFloor, Gym, Basement, HerOffice, 3rdFloor, Livingroom, OutdoorBackyard, HisOffice in-wall) — repatriated to a local controller running on Rocinante at `https://192.168.1.171:8443`. Done without factory-resetting any device, without admin to the Verizon Fios router, and without involving BHS. Method: read each AP's `mgmt.authkey` via `ubnt:ubnt` SSH, pre-seed our controller's MongoDB with a `device` record carrying the BHS authkey, persist a boot-time iptables block of the BHS controller IP via `iptables.{i}.cmd` config key, then `syswrapper.sh save-config && apply-config` and `syswrapper.sh set-adopt http://192.168.1.171:8080/inform <authkey>`. HisOffice (G7IW model) required a `firmware.json` patch aliasing `G7IW` to `U7PIW`'s firmware bundle plus a controller restart. Livingroom recovered via U-PoE++ injector power-cycle (separate brick from switch PoE). PSKs rotated (`Berman Net` → `MapleStreet-Sunset19!`, `GhLoP` PSK rotated then reverted at Aneeta's request to her chosen passphrase, eventually consolidated to single `LGP123` SSID); WPA2-PSK upgraded to WPA3-SAE + WPA2 transition with `pmf_mode=optional`. Phase 3 partial: 2.4 GHz channels pinned 1/6/11 (3B), 6 GHz enabled, auto-firmware-update window verified at 3 AM release-channel (3D). VLAN segmentation (3A) and IPv6 firewall audit (3C) deferred. Daily `.unf` backup wired via `scripts/unifi-daily-backup.ps1` + Windows Scheduled Task "UniFi Daily Backup" at 3 AM ET, writing to `C:\Users\alto8\backups\unifi\` (local, 30-day rolling) + SCP off-site to rtxserver `/home/alton/sartor-network-backups/`. 13 child docs filed under `projects/unifi-takeover-2026-05-01-*`, indexed via [[unifi-takeover-2026-05-01-INDEX]]. Network renamed Sartor-Saxena-Claude Network. Pete email drafted in Gmail (draft id `r1648436912190611604`), awaiting Alton's send. Open follow-ups: physical Nest retirement once family migrates to LGP123, `mgmt_url`/`stun_url` audit on remaining APs, `letmeinnow` hidden-SSID confirmation, DNS filter and UCG-Pro decisions, Phase 3A/C. [[reference_home_network]] updated to reflect the new topology. Backup directory README written at `C:\Users\alto8\backups\unifi\README.md`. `ap-authkeys-2026-05-01.json` is treated like `.ssh/` — outside repo, never committed.
